SIMPLE: usquebaugh
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usquebaugh
<hw>Us"que*baugh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ir. or Gael.
<ets>uisge beatha</ets>, literally, water of life; <ets>uisge</ets>
water + <ets>beatha</ets> life; akin to Gr. <grk>bi`os</grk> life. See
<er>Quick</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Whisky</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A compound distilled spirit made in Ireland and
Scotland; whisky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Scottish returns being vested in grouse, white hares, pickled
salmon, and <qex>usquebaugh</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A liquor compounded of brandy, or other strong
spirit, raisins, cinnamon and other spices.</def> <rj><au>Brande &
C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usself</ent>⟦br⟧
